
[1]scissors

   SCISSORS, n. siz'zors, plu. [L. scissor, from scindo, to cut, Gr.]

   A cutting instrument resembling shears, but smaller, consisting of two
   cutting blades movable on a pin in the center, by which they are
   fastened. Hence we usually say, a pair of scissors.
